name: Tom Daley
summary: Olympic diver Tom Daley has announced his return to diving in preparation for the 2024 Paris Olympics. Daley, who won gold in Tokyo last year, visited the Olympic Village in Paris to test out the cardboard beds that will be used by athletes. He also discussed his childhood dream of competing in the Olympics and the significance of diving in front of his family. Daley is currently 30 years old and married to Dustin Lance Black, with whom he has two children. Despite his age, he remains confident in his ability to defend his Olympic title and overcome his biggest threat, which he has not yet disclosed publicly.

summary: Ted Baker, a renowned fashion retailer, is reportedly facing imminent closures of all its UK stores. The arrests stem from an alleged ruse, with "El Chapo's" son reportedly luring Zambada into the US before their apprehension. These arrests mark a significant development in the fight against drug trafficking, as Zambada has long been a central figure in the Sinaloa cartel's operations.

name: Eswatini
summary: Eswatini is making efforts to strengthen its relationships with Asian countries, while carefully navigating the diplomatic challenges between China and Taiwan. The country is also exploring the potential of coffee production to drive socio-economic development. However, there are concerns about potential human rights violations as Eswatini works to regulate its ICT sector. Calls have been made to ensure privacy and security in the national ID system digitization process. Capacity building initiatives are underway to support local government authorities. The tourism industry is expected to receive a boost from a new visa-free travel policy for citizens of 93 countries. The country's official name has been changed from Swaziland to Eswatini, and it will participate in the 2024 Paris Olympics under the code "SWZ." Additionally, UNICEF is supporting solar energy initiatives in Eswatini, and a missionary alumnus has returned to serve in the country's ministry.
